<TEXT>
 american businessman edmond pope has been found guilty of espionage in a
 russian court.
 he's been sentenced to <TIMEX2 val="P20Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">20 years in prison</TIMEX2>.
 pope was charged with trying to buy classified information on a russian
 torpedo.
 he maintains the data had been previously published and sold abroad.
 the <TIMEX2 val="P54Y" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="2000" anchor_dir="ENDING" comment="">54-year-old</TIMEX2> has a rare form of bone cancer.
 pope's wife and u.s. officials have been calling for his release.
 his attorneys have <TIMEX2 val="P7D" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="2000-12-06" anchor_dir="STARTING" comment="possibly starting 2000-12-07">seven days</TIMEX2> to appeal the sentence.
</TEXT>
